==English==

===Pronunciation===
*moh-hah-doh

===Noun===
'''mojado'''  (''plural:'' '''[[mojados]]''') is a derogatory term for a [[Mexican]] or Central American who [[illegal]]ly enters the [[United States of America]] from its southern border, often by either [[swim]]ming or wading across the [[w:Rio Grande|Rio Grande]]. 

The Spanish-language translation ''espalda mojada'' &ndash; or, more tersely, ''mojado'' &ndash; is used in a similar sense by [[Hispanic |Hispanic American]]s. ''Espalda mojada'' is also used in an equally pejorative way in [[Spain]] to refer to illegal immigrants from [[Morocco]] who cross the [[w:Straits of Gibraltar|Straits of Gibraltar]].

It is used interchangeably with the [[English language|English]] term, [[wetback]].

